45:45.042 --> 45:47.011 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
JEFFREY BROWN: Barak Goodman is
the director
of the film "Oklahoma City."

45:47.044 --> 45:51.482 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
BARAK GOODMAN: While I think a
lot of people
remember this as a simple story
of a lone

45:51.515 --> 45:55.586 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
terrorist committing an act, it
actually has
very deep roots.

45:55.620 --> 46:00.091 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
And when we pulled on those
roots, a whole
'nother story sort of appeared.

46:00.124 --> 46:04.795 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JEFFREY BROWN: The film delves
into the rise
of white nationalist militias in
the 1980s,

46:04.829 --> 46:10.701 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
and two later events that
galvanized the country
and deeply influenced Oklahoma
City bomber

46:10.735 --> 46:20.211 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Timothy McVeigh: the siege of
